The privatisation of Bromley's entire housing stock was the first and the largest exercise of its kind. There were a number of apparent irregularities in the process, arguably setting dangerous precedents:-
1) Public servants, Bromley Council housing officers, were actively involved in canvassing for the transfer, an apparent breach of normal protocol requiring public servants to be apolitical;
2) The 'election' was one-sided, with glossy literature on one side only, this deemed wrong by the UN.
